<subSubSection id="0A58DF6219E9002F33B9281236EF7666" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FBB43459A2A82F898FBCC232CECE60AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9EF9C297BD3E64416E347A59389475D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active from late spring till early summer and range in total length 4.5-7.5 mm and 1.5-3 mm in maximum width. They are readily attracted to artificial lights at night, but are also active during daytime when they can be observed crawling and mating on dead tree twigs and branches. In nearby Hong Kong, where in the past this species has been erroneously reported as 
<taxonomicName id="047B1B1CA5B1DFCA06E32F57E4E17628" genus="E." lsidName="E. guttulatus subsp. subconjunctus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="subSpecies" species="guttulatus" subSpecies="subconjunctus">
<emphasis id="49AB8F708C629B371F61760267558351" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">E. guttulatus subconjunctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the larval host plants include 
<taxonomicName id="AEEF81F4E08EF910F52C6770C14A1305" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acacia farnesiana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="farnesiana">
<emphasis id="EB0EAE67ED7A6B68ED31EF4E4D018FD2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Acacia farnesiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B53582EA4147488D07DF59DCEFF9545A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Osmeridae" genus="Mallotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mallotus" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="553085A42D28063BE78FD0B2CC3AB164" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mallotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName id="EC0A77D8E5B0453D61880F8523D39C7E" class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Morus alba" order="Ciconiiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="650010505A34A7A200F2B2B06EEE42C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Morus alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1BB7A527DE27F4D51E40AA5A2730C517" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="61DFA556E77566F147771A5587F5DFB0" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B162" refString="Yiu, V, Yip, CH, 2011. A Photographic Guide to Hong Kong Beetles, Part 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="A Photographic Guide to Hong Kong Beetles, Part 1." year="2011">Yiu and Yip 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
